data.name: labelCowDesc.Text
data.value: Cows are large domesticated animals known for their gentle nature. They are raised primarily for their milk, which is used to produce dairy products such as cheese, butter, and yogurt. Cows graze on grass and enjoy a calm, social life in herds.

data.name: labelBeeDesc.Text
data.value: Bees are small flying insects that play a crucial role in pollination. They collect nectar from flowers and transform it into honey, a sweet and natural food. Bees live in colonies and work together to maintain their hive and care for their young.

data.name: labelChickenDesc.Text
data.value: Chickens are domesticated birds commonly raised for their eggs and meat. They lay eggs almost daily under the right conditions. Chickens are social animals, often scratching the ground to find food and enjoying sunshine and outdoor spaces.

data.name: labelGoatDesc.Text
data.value: Goats are curious and agile animals often kept on farms. They produce nutritious milk that can be consumed directly or used to make cheese and other dairy products. Goats are hardy and can adapt to various climates and terrains.

data.name: labelLambDesc.Text
data.value: Lambs are young sheep known for their soft and fluffy wool. They grow up to produce wool that can be spun into yarn for clothing and textiles. Lambs are gentle, playful animals that often graze in grassy pastures with their flock.
